The paper deals with machine learning algorithms for crowdsourced learning tasks, specifically linear regression. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with subjective features, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of photos as input data suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another possible sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of culturally fraught features, which could fall under social and information retrieval (cs.SI) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
